        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 8 at 3:16PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>At 315 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 9
miles south of Plentywood, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Plentywood, Medicine Lake, Froid, Westby, Archer, Port Of Raymond,
Outlook, Reserve, Raymond, Dagmar, Homestead, Dooley, Comertown,
Antelope, and Coalridge.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
